post_text:
At last night's school board meeting, board members were introduced to new RCS Director of Dining Services, Quill Redwine. Mr. Redwine is the main contact person for Chartwells K12.

Mr. Redwine is originally from San Antonio, Texas, and went to school on a track & field and academic scholarship through the University of Notre Dame, earning a B.B.A. in Entrepreneurial Management, in 2002, and a Master of Arts in Ministry in 2017 from Indiana Wesleyan University. He has worked as a general manager and training manager for a number of big box retailers before obtaining licenses for selling stocks as a Stock Broker for Charles Schwab. During his time at Schwab, he joined the U.S. Army and served for more than 6 years. A little more than three years ago, he took over as the Director of Catering and Concessions for Warren Township.

Please join us in welcoming Mr. Redwine as the new RCS Director of Dining Services. #Welcome

post_text:
We have some preschool openings! Choose from morning (8:30 a.m.- 11 a.m.) or afternoon (12 - 2:30 p.m.) classes.

All RCS preschool programs use the same curriculum and deliver the same high-quality early childhood experience.

Preschool classes are located at Charles, Crestdale, Starr, Fairview, Vaile, and Westview Elementary Schools.

Our Early Childhood Special Education classrooms will be located at Crestdale.

For the most part, students will be placed in preschool programs in the buildings determined by their residence based
on established attendance boundaries. Students whose IEP recommends placement in the ECSE setting will be
placed at Crestdale. Transportation will be provided for these students only.

Eligible students who are not enrolled will be placed on a waiting list, and enrollment will be made based upon the priority guidelines. You will be contacted by your school to confirm your status and to complete the enrollment process. We look forward to meeting you!
http://www.rcs.k12.in.us/files/Preschool%20Application%20Form%202016-2017.pdf

post_text:
Wayne County's public schools receive $779,100 grant to help students have more access to remote learning

– On Wednesday, Governor Eric Holcolm announced
that Richmond Community Schools, Western Wayne Schools, Nettle Creek School Corporation, Northeastern Wayne Schools, and Centerville-Abington Schools have been awarded $779,100 through the Governor’s Emergency Education Relief Fund (GEER).

The emergency education relief fund was created with money from the federal CARES Act. The award includes funding for student devices, teacher devices, and connectivity.

“I appreciate the combined group effort, collaboration, and support,” said @Jennifer O’Brien, RCS Interim Superintendent. “I believe partnering together, along with letters of support from the Economic Development Corporation of Wayne County, the Wayne
County Board of Commissioners, and Communities In Schools of Wayne County helped secure this grant for our community.”

http://www.rcs.k12.in.us/files/GEER%20grant.pdf

From Mr. Jimmy Bailey:

Hello Facebook friends! I am the head football coach for the 7th and 8th Grade Red Devil Football program. We will start July 21 from 6 p.m. - 7:30 p.m on the high school grass field. Make sure your child comes with gym shorts, a t-shirt, cleats/running shoes, and their own water bottle. Paperwork for student-athletes will be handed out upon arrival. Coaches will be wearing masks during practice. Players are not required to wear a mask. However, they are asked to wear one before and after practice. We are welcome to any student that wishes to be a manager as well. We can’t wait to meet our student-athletes! If you have questions or concerns please email IRFcoach@gmail.com or message me directly. Red Devil Pride! 😈💯🏈

post_text:
RCS School Board announces indication of Intent to Resign by Superintendent Dr. Todd Terrill

RICHMOND, June 26, 2020 – RCS Superintendent Dr. Todd Terrill has notified the Board of School Trustees of his intent to resign from his position. The intent to resign will be based on pending approval for a position in another school district. Formal action on his letter of resignation will be considered at a later time.

It is not immediately clear when Dr. Terrill’s last day will be or who will be appointed as interim superintendent after his departure.

http://www.rcs.k12.in.us/files/Terrill%20Intent%20to%20Resign%20Press%20Release.pdf

shared_text:
Edward Junior‎Richmond Community Schools
May 20 at 7:02 PM · Richmond, IN ·

Had the privilege today of attending my nieces Graduation Moment today! I used the word "Moment" because that is what it was.

But it was her "Moment" and our "Moment" to see her go across the stage and receive what she worked so hard for. Her parents were there, her grandparents were there, her family were there, others who influenced her were there, and the staff of Richmond High School were there.

In all her glory she was given a Moment to share this great accomplishment with the people who cared and supported her through the journey.

Was it perfect? I have to say yes it was, given the restrictions placed on schools it was perfect! The staff worked tirelessly to make it perfect. The staff rallied around these high school graduates like they were their own children.

People seem to always head to the computer when they are unhappy, we need more people sharing why and what makes them happy about a person, place, or thing.

Thank You Richmond Senior High School for going above and beyond to create around 250 "Moments!" for the graduates and families of the RHS Class of 2020.

We R Proud of Daniel Barbre! Daniel has been a member of concert band for 7 years and the marching band for 5 years. He is a percussionist whose band accomplishments include Band Captain, Section Leader of bass drums for two years, two percussion captions, and two gold state solo and ensemble medals. Congratulations to our 2020 Band Graduate, Daniel!

Fairview Elementary School
May 1 at 3:50 PM ·

Perfect Circle Credit Union generously donated Fire 7 tablets to help out with some of our students who do not have devices for get extended learning done. Thank you so much to PCCU. They had planned to sponsor a field trip for us this year, but when plans changed they still chose to back us. They are phenomenal! Mrs. Plank will be distributing these devices to some families on Monday after they are set up. Calls will be made to the families who are receiving the tablets. @weRrichmond #fairviewlions

P.S. I can't believe that some come with Mrs. Plank's face as the wallpaper. :)

Jared Shields
April 30 at 5:19 PM ·

Richmond Community! Join me in supporting Richmond High School Athletics and fighting against COVID-19 by signing up for the #RackFromHome challenge by Rack Performance! If you sign up you'll get 21 days of workouts sent to your phone via the Rack Performance App, a t-shirt, and get to support Richmond Athletics. If we get enough people to sign up we could get our 1-year subscription to Rack Performance for free! Money raised from this challenge will go to Heart to Heart International to help fight against COVID-19. So make sure to sign-up, get stronger together, and help raise money for a good cause!

https://docs.google.com/document/d/1iyQJ-zTtyuMrZg-W7IWhsLH-4huQk00HbtZ432a5Ifo/edit?usp=sharing
http://go.rackperformance.com/rack-from-home-challenge

Any student currently in 5th, 6th, or 7th grade is eligible to attend a FREE day camp on the Earlham College campus from July 27-31. Earlham faculty and graduate students pursuing a teaching degree will assist students in being History Mythbusters!

➡️increase their capacity to work with digital media thoughtfully

➡️engage in team-building activities to promote leadership skills

➡️have fun learning inside and outside
